1
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:00,009
[The Promise of the Soul]

2
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:04,980
[Episode 8: Was that person really you?]

3
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:23,439
Yu Chan.

4
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:44,950
Yu Chan.

5
00:01:45,530 --> 00:01:47,599
Why are your eyebrows thicker?

6
00:01:48,439 --> 00:01:50,340
And your nose higher?

7
00:02:15,069 --> 00:02:16,129
Why did you kiss me?

8
00:02:16,419 --> 00:02:18,030
You kissed me first.

9
00:02:20,539 --> 00:02:22,199
That was a misunderstanding.

10
00:02:25,139 --> 00:02:26,199
Explain yourself.

11
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:29,079
I just had a dream.

12
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:30,650
I dreamed of my wife.

13
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:33,870
And you both happen
to have a mole on your face.

14
00:02:33,969 --> 00:02:35,430
I mixed you up for a moment.

15
00:02:35,469 --> 00:02:37,129
You're using me as a stand-in.

16
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:39,990
No, no.

17
00:02:40,689 --> 00:02:42,090
Honestly,

18
00:02:42,759 --> 00:02:45,270
sometimes I see a red string on my hand.

19
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:48,629
And it's tied to yours.

20
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:50,110
So…

21
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:52,990
I suspect you're my wife's reincarnation.

22
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,849
I'm this guy's wife?

23
00:02:59,770 --> 00:03:01,370
Did you see that red string?

24
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:10,039
I'm confused too.

25
00:03:11,229 --> 00:03:13,289
We're both guys,

26
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:14,849
how could that be possible?

27
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:15,719
So what?

28
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,060
Possible or not,

29
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,150
you won't know unless you try.

30
00:03:22,099 --> 00:03:23,789
When I kissed you just now,

31
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:25,280
did you feel anything?

32
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:29,669
Just now…

33
00:03:30,409 --> 00:03:32,009
I was still half-asleep.

34
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,340
Then now that you're awake.

35
00:03:36,139 --> 00:03:37,069
What do you want?

36
00:03:37,219 --> 00:03:38,379
Kiss you again to find out.

37
00:03:38,379 --> 00:03:39,780
No way.

38
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,180
Why not?

39
00:03:44,569 --> 00:03:46,439
I've been married to a woman.

40
00:03:46,849 --> 00:03:48,860
How could I be with a man?

41
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,740
That's why we need to try.

42
00:03:54,349 --> 00:03:55,590
No way.

43
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,539
As long as you feel something, it's fine.

44
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:03,030
I don't dare.

45
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,500
I'm not used to it.

46
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:08,449
Then why are you so used to
sleeping while holding me?

47
00:04:17,149 --> 00:04:18,790
What if I don't like it?

48
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,300
If you don't like it,

49
00:04:24,329 --> 00:04:25,829
I won't force you again.

50
00:04:29,990 --> 00:04:31,160
Didn't you say

51
00:04:31,189 --> 00:04:32,990
we're connected by a red string?

52
00:04:33,939 --> 00:04:35,000
Aren't you curious

53
00:04:35,490 --> 00:04:37,029
what that means?

54
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:51,850
You could have
cleared that stage yesterday.

55
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:54,250
Why did you call me
in the middle of the night to help you?

56
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:56,319
Don't ask, you'll be scared.

57
00:04:57,850 --> 00:04:58,908
Or…

58
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:01,660
Should I move in and sleep with you?

59
00:05:05,689 --> 00:05:07,350
So yesterday was a rehearsal?

60
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:12,129
We haven't even started dating,
and we've already slept together?

61
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,430
What are you thinking?

62
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:15,670
That's because…

63
00:05:16,509 --> 00:05:17,310
There was a cockroach on my bed.

64
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:18,569
I didn't dare sleep alone.

65
00:05:18,569 --> 00:05:19,629
That's easy to fix.

66
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:20,620
I'll go to your room later

67
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:22,350
and kill the cockroach for you.

68
00:05:25,149 --> 00:05:27,040
Forget it if you don't want.
I'll find someone else.

69
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,970
You can't sleep with someone else.

70
00:05:29,439 --> 00:05:31,699
Chen Qiansui,
you just can't sleep with someone else.

71
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:32,800
Did you hear me?

72
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:47,970
See, I'm this close to you,

73
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,730
and you're not pushing me away.

74
00:05:50,329 --> 00:05:52,550
How can we bravely try?

75
00:05:55,639 --> 00:05:57,269
Then try bravely just once.

76
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:59,750
How can we bravely
try something like this?

77
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,790
Try what bravely?

78
00:06:01,889 --> 00:06:02,920
Try what bravely?

79
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,310
Swimming.

80
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,199
Bravely try swimming.

81
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:13,870
Wait.

82
00:06:13,889 --> 00:06:14,790
Say that again.

83
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,069
I want to record it.

84
00:06:17,860 --> 00:06:18,379
Come on.

85
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:24,709
I will bravely try swimming.

86
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:28,670
If it's mine, it's mine.

87
00:06:29,199 --> 00:06:31,000
Let's see how long you can dodge.

88
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:32,819
Off to swim.

89
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:33,930
Qiansui, save me.

90
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:35,220
I'm not going to swim.

91
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,290
You already promised me.

92
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:37,759
-Let's go to the pool.
-Let go.

93
00:06:37,759 --> 00:06:38,930
Come on, hurry.

94
00:06:38,930 --> 00:06:40,029
I can't swim.

95
00:06:40,029 --> 00:06:40,959
You can swim.

96
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:42,259
Let go, let go.

97
00:06:42,259 --> 00:06:43,600
Don't squat down, come on.

98
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,800
Let's go.

99
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,550
Help!

100
00:06:46,069 --> 00:06:47,639
Come on, hurry.

101
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:49,779
Let me go.

102
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,540
Xia Zefang.

103
00:06:52,209 --> 00:06:53,110
Xia Zefang.

104
00:06:53,529 --> 00:06:54,589
Come here a second.

105
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,680
The teacher's calling me.

106
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:01,370
Sir, this way please.

107
00:07:01,810 --> 00:07:03,259
Finally caught him.

108
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:05,829
Forced fruit isn't sweet.

109
00:07:05,829 --> 00:07:08,560
Wait until he figures it out himself,
he'll come.

110
00:07:15,779 --> 00:07:17,639
Last time you told me not to worry,

111
00:07:18,139 --> 00:07:19,839
and you volunteered to learn.

112
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:22,470
I thought you'd be a natural.

113
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,470
Couldn't you tell I was joking?

114
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,670
I take everything you say seriously.

115
00:07:26,670 --> 00:07:27,129
Come on.

116
00:07:27,399 --> 00:07:28,560
I don't want to.

117
00:07:28,589 --> 00:07:29,790
Hurry.

118
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:30,879
Don't squat like him.

119
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:31,980
Move faster.

120
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:33,459
You said it yourself last time.

121
00:07:33,459 --> 00:07:34,569
Come on, let's go.

122
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,860
At worst, you can do it.

123
00:07:51,620 --> 00:07:53,720
Rare to see you so down.

124
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,740
Did your Ye ignore you?

125
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:59,579
How could he ignore me?

126
00:08:00,110 --> 00:08:02,540
He's just afraid
that after seeing my grades,

127
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:03,769
he'll want to dump me.

128
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,089
No way.

129
00:08:06,709 --> 00:08:07,689
I think you two

130
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:08,920
are fated.

131
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:11,079
You can see it?

132
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,350
See what?

133
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:19,089
See your Ye coming back.

134
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:23,569
Do you believe in lovers from a past life?

135
00:08:24,870 --> 00:08:25,870
Why not?

136
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,740
If you find them,

137
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,220
shouldn't you hold on?

138
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,490
But…

139
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:34,740
What if you've got the wrong person?

140
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:37,048
What if I miss them?

141
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:54,850
Missing them is better
than never experiencing it.

142
00:08:57,779 --> 00:08:58,789
So much food...

143
00:08:59,559 --> 00:09:00,759
How much for one bowl?

144
00:09:01,379 --> 00:09:02,080
No idea.

145
00:09:02,529 --> 00:09:03,860
A customer gave it to me.

146
00:09:04,409 --> 00:09:05,740
A female customer?

147
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,639
Up to no good?

148
00:09:08,549 --> 00:09:09,740
Giving young men

149
00:09:09,779 --> 00:09:10,779
oysters at night.

150
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:20,419
Too bad…

151
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:22,029
I don't eat shellfish.

152
00:09:22,539 --> 00:09:23,409
You finish it.

153
00:09:27,929 --> 00:09:30,330
Next time don't bring back
late-night snacks.

154
00:09:30,330 --> 00:09:31,460
They'll make me fat.

155
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,340
Maybe because Xia Zefang keeps swimming.

156
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:38,509
But you don't.

157
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:43,870
Then why's your body so good

158
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:46,279
if you don't swim?

159
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:08,879
Don't run off every time you grope me.

160
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:37,639
Why's your heart beating so fast?

161
00:10:52,769 --> 00:10:54,259
Qiansui's not coming back tonight.

162
00:10:54,259 --> 00:10:55,460
I'll sleep in his bed.

163
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:57,620
Finally no more floor mattress.

164
00:10:59,019 --> 00:10:59,950
Nervous?

165
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:03,389
It's not like
we haven't been alone before.

166
00:11:04,059 --> 00:11:04,889
Or…

167
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:10,610
Do you feel different about me?

168
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:13,980
I haven't showered yet.

169
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:15,169
I'll go shower.

170
00:11:22,009 --> 00:11:23,269
Why is your face so red?

171
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,610
Must be from that bowl
of oysters just now.

172
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:30,080
Just youthful energy and a healthy body.

173
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:30,899
Healthy body.

174
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:36,990
What do you think I'm going to do?

175
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,330
You're so close,

176
00:11:40,779 --> 00:11:42,379
like you're about to kiss me.

177
00:11:44,779 --> 00:11:45,440
You want it?

178
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,049
Since you saw the red string,

179
00:11:51,769 --> 00:11:54,500
and someone at the temple
was promoting it today,

180
00:11:54,710 --> 00:11:56,360
I happened to have it
blessed in the temple fire

181
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,240
for safety.

182
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,740
Then…

183
00:12:03,659 --> 00:12:05,519
Why do you have one too?

184
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,480
Can't I have protection?

185
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:08,840
Sure…

186
00:12:09,289 --> 00:12:11,820
But I'm afraid people
will misunderstand us.

187
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:12,860
What,

188
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:14,090
is that not okay?

189
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:16,659
Didn't you say we're tied by a red string?

190
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,850
Wouldn't blocking your admirers
be a good thing?

191
00:12:20,299 --> 00:12:21,299
Then give it back.

192
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:22,370
Once given, it's given.

193
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:23,830
Why would you take it back?

194
00:12:24,529 --> 00:12:27,460
I just don't want people
saying bad things about you.

195
00:12:31,710 --> 00:12:32,679
If it's you,

196
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,970
then who cares if they talk?

197
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:39,049
Why are you so good to me?

198
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:43,210
I told you,

199
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,220
because it's you.

200
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,769
Come down and swim.

201
00:12:55,769 --> 00:12:56,500
I don't want to.

202
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,440
Please.

203
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,470
No.

204
00:12:58,470 --> 00:12:59,539
Come swim.

205
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,480
Come on, you're already in swim trunks.

206
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,509
You forced me into them.

207
00:13:02,509 --> 00:13:03,809
I think you need to be braver.

208
00:13:03,809 --> 00:13:04,509
Braver.

209
00:13:04,509 --> 00:13:05,409
I'll be with you.

210
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:06,049
Come on.

211
00:13:06,049 --> 00:13:07,480
Go be brave yourself. Why pull me in?

212
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:09,519
I want to swim with you.

213
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:15,259
That hurts.

214
00:13:15,289 --> 00:13:16,110
Are you okay?

215
00:13:16,389 --> 00:13:18,500
Easy for you to say.
You can do it, of course it's easy.

216
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,360
I'm here.

217
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,889
I think you need to be braver.

218
00:13:20,889 --> 00:13:22,899
With you here, I still choked last time.

219
00:13:22,899 --> 00:13:24,200
I drank the whole pool.

220
00:13:24,659 --> 00:13:26,279
You still remember something
from junior high school?

221
00:13:26,279 --> 00:13:27,000
What else?

222
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,500
You always force me like this.

223
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,649
You only choked on one mouthful.

224
00:13:29,649 --> 00:13:30,870
And you let go yourself.

225
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:32,340
No way, you let go.

226
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:33,539
You let go. How could I have let go?

227
00:13:33,539 --> 00:13:35,200
The pool's completely empty.

228
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,899
Xia Zefang's here.

229
00:13:40,009 --> 00:13:41,279
It's not open on weekends.

230
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:42,620
But I made an exception for Qiansui.

231
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:43,379
For me?

232
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:46,320
You're waiting for Xia Zefang, aren't you?

233
00:13:52,460 --> 00:13:53,529
Are you hungry?

234
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,690
I'll make you instant noodles.

235
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:07,649
So you came anyway.

236
00:14:08,129 --> 00:14:10,190
Didn't you say you're scared to swim?

237
00:14:12,049 --> 00:14:12,950
When I was a kid,

238
00:14:13,409 --> 00:14:15,139
someone drowned in front of me.

239
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,120
I tried to save him,

240
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:19,289
but I almost...

241
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,220
In the end,

242
00:14:22,759 --> 00:14:24,429
we didn't save him.

243
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:27,620
Ever since, I've been afraid of water.

244
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:29,799
Now I just take baths at most.

245
00:14:31,529 --> 00:14:34,169
Right now, this body is Xia Zefang's,

246
00:14:34,529 --> 00:14:35,899
but the soul is Xia Cha.

247
00:14:37,769 --> 00:14:39,909
If Xia Zefang comes back for his body,

248
00:14:40,169 --> 00:14:41,179
who could win?

249
00:14:41,809 --> 00:14:42,809
Why fight over it?

250
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:44,379
Just give it back.

251
00:14:46,539 --> 00:14:48,070
If it were me,

252
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,779
I'd feel it was such a waste.

253
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:55,519
If Zefang comes back,

254
00:14:56,289 --> 00:14:57,559
treat him well.

255
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,960
People probably want you back more.

256
00:15:00,559 --> 00:15:01,299
After all,

257
00:15:01,759 --> 00:15:03,059
the current Xia Zefang

258
00:15:03,059 --> 00:15:04,519
is much cuter than before.

259
00:15:06,129 --> 00:15:07,860
Zefang wasn't that bad, was he?

260
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,200
Wait.

261
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:11,240
Now the only people

262
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,570
in the world who think

263
00:15:12,659 --> 00:15:15,259
Xia Zefang's a good guy
are you and Guan Riqing.

264
00:15:25,470 --> 00:15:26,870
Come on, lower your body.

265
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:28,659
Let's push down.

266
00:15:28,659 --> 00:15:29,620
Yes, yes, twist your waist.

267
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:30,789
Body sideways a bit.

268
00:15:30,789 --> 00:15:31,690
Yes, sideways.

269
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,759
Good, arms straight.

270
00:15:32,759 --> 00:15:33,559
Stretch.

271
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:36,700
Like this?

272
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:40,799
Didn't expect you
to forget even the basic warm-up.

273
00:15:40,799 --> 00:15:42,299
No wonder you said you couldn't swim.

274
00:15:42,299 --> 00:15:44,230
I thought you were making excuses.

275
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:47,110
So don't expect too much

276
00:15:47,110 --> 00:15:48,610
from how well I'll swim.

277
00:15:49,580 --> 00:15:52,409
Why do Qiansui and Haiyuan call you Cha?

278
00:15:54,779 --> 00:15:56,019
This time I went back,

279
00:15:56,070 --> 00:15:57,190
because of Grandpa's passing,

280
00:15:57,190 --> 00:15:58,120
to remember him,

281
00:15:58,289 --> 00:16:00,220
I decided to use his name,

282
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,190
a fresh start.

283
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:06,500
You're really much better than before now.

284
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:09,350
Was I really that bad before?

285
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,299
Hearing that your Cha's here

286
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:28,409
made you rush over.

287
00:16:28,649 --> 00:16:29,379
I was nearby.

288
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,840
So this is what you're like
when you're in love.

289
00:16:40,539 --> 00:16:41,409
I'm not.

290
00:16:44,929 --> 00:16:47,029
The way you look at someone
you like never changes.

291
00:16:47,029 --> 00:16:48,690
Look at how you look at him now.

292
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:53,210
Bend lower.

293
00:16:53,259 --> 00:16:54,389
Yes, arms like this.

294
00:16:54,549 --> 00:16:55,370
Pull your arms in.

295
00:16:55,370 --> 00:16:56,500
Yes, hold your arms.

296
00:16:56,509 --> 00:16:57,179
Hold arms?

297
00:17:02,379 --> 00:17:04,318
You should see how you look at him.

298
00:17:07,618 --> 00:17:09,078
I'm afraid you'll hit him.

299
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:13,650
You should be honest, too.

300
00:17:14,118 --> 00:17:16,049
Watch out or he'll get stolen away.

301
00:17:25,490 --> 00:17:26,390
Zefang,

302
00:17:26,868 --> 00:17:28,068
I was afraid of water.

303
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:29,380
But you're not.

304
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:30,809
This is your body.

305
00:17:31,309 --> 00:17:32,369
When I let go later,

306
00:17:32,549 --> 00:17:33,779
you have to hold on.

307
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,000
Chen Qiansui,

308
00:17:58,309 --> 00:17:59,809
if Xia Zefang can, you can too.

309
00:17:59,809 --> 00:18:00,390
Come on in.

310
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:00,960
I don't want to.

311
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,579
Your swim team isn't short on new members.

312
00:18:02,579 --> 00:18:03,410
Hurry.

313
00:18:03,859 --> 00:18:05,240
What are you doing?

314
00:18:05,269 --> 00:18:06,930
Still running? Get back here.

315
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:09,900
Attacking me?

316
00:18:26,630 --> 00:18:27,900
Did you see that just now?

317
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:28,859
I can swim.

318
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,740
I can swim!

319
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:31,670
Let's go eat.

320
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,430
But I want to swim a bit more.

321
00:18:34,339 --> 00:18:35,640
You haven't swum in so long,

322
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,599
and you just hit the back of your head.

323
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:39,000
That's enough for today.

324
00:18:39,349 --> 00:18:41,680
I'll take you somewhere delicious, okay?

325
00:18:41,710 --> 00:18:42,269
Okay.

326
00:18:42,289 --> 00:18:43,220
Then wait for me.

327
00:18:47,589 --> 00:18:48,250
Wait for me.

328
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:13,950
Ye Haiyuan.

329
00:19:16,269 --> 00:19:17,430
That tickles!

330
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,079
Let me rinse off first, okay?

331
00:19:27,349 --> 00:19:29,079
Ye Haiyuan, what are you doing?

332
00:19:44,059 --> 00:19:45,259
Stop hitting him!

333
00:19:45,289 --> 00:19:47,450
Jiang Bailing, Chen Qiansui!

334
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:54,430
Stop hitting him.

335
00:19:54,450 --> 00:19:56,349
You're not a fighting dog.

336
00:20:03,859 --> 00:20:04,859
What's wrong?

337
00:20:12,910 --> 00:20:13,740
Ye Haiyuan.

338
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,210
What?

339
00:20:17,670 --> 00:20:18,380
Haiyuan!

340
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:19,880
Ye Haiyuan!

341
00:20:21,329 --> 00:20:22,359
Ye Haiyuan!

342
00:20:22,450 --> 00:20:23,680
Come here.

343
00:20:25,549 --> 00:20:27,089
Can you stop being so childish?

344
00:20:27,089 --> 00:20:28,259
Hitting without asking,

345
00:20:28,259 --> 00:20:29,190
then turning away?

346
00:20:29,190 --> 00:20:30,259
He's more mature?

347
00:20:30,690 --> 00:20:31,759
Then go to him.

348
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,109
Ye Haiyuan.

349
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:35,160
Are you crazy?

350
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:35,980
Yes.

351
00:20:36,259 --> 00:20:37,319
The crazy one is me.

352
00:20:38,069 --> 00:20:39,599
I thought I mattered to you.

353
00:20:39,990 --> 00:20:40,890
And?

354
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:42,950
And what?

355
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:44,329
What did you see?

356
00:20:47,619 --> 00:20:49,650
I had soap all over my head.

357
00:20:49,670 --> 00:20:51,140
I couldn't see who it was.

358
00:20:51,539 --> 00:20:53,789
You couldn’t even see,
and you were still that passionate?

359
00:20:53,789 --> 00:20:54,630
Or maybe…

360
00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:56,849
This body likes him more.

361
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,650
Why are you saying things so nasty?

362
00:21:05,789 --> 00:21:07,119
I thought it was you.

363
00:21:08,529 --> 00:21:10,200
There was no one else in the pool.

364
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,529
Who else would do that

365
00:21:11,529 --> 00:21:12,329
to me there?

366
00:21:12,789 --> 00:21:14,519
How do I know it was Guan Riqing?

367
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,140
How can you not tell the difference?

368
00:21:20,519 --> 00:21:21,230
Or…

369
00:21:21,769 --> 00:21:23,900
Are we not close enough for you to tell?

370
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:36,119
How are you
any different from Guan Riqing?

371
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,630
Just because you know my secret

372
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:44,059
doesn't mean
you can treat me however you want.

373
00:21:45,599 --> 00:21:47,460
I don't want to argue with you now.

374
00:21:49,289 --> 00:21:50,750
Let's cool off for a while.

375
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:05,410
[Got the question wrong,
wrote the wrong answer, not my intention.]

376
00:22:05,410 --> 00:22:07,630
[Can you not be so mad?]

377
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,920
Sir, I'm really happy to see you.

378
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,089
Wait, wait.

379
00:22:11,089 --> 00:22:12,660
I've never seen the teacher

380
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:14,119
so popular with students.

381
00:22:14,210 --> 00:22:15,950
Sir, any instructions?

382
00:22:16,329 --> 00:22:17,400
One good news,

383
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,329
one bad news.

384
00:22:18,630 --> 00:22:19,430
Congratulations,

385
00:22:19,430 --> 00:22:21,339
you won an award for calligraphy.

386
00:22:23,490 --> 00:22:24,589
That's great!

387
00:22:24,609 --> 00:22:25,630
I didn't expect it.

388
00:22:25,630 --> 00:22:27,130
And one bad news.

389
00:22:29,519 --> 00:22:30,849
You didn't do

390
00:22:30,869 --> 00:22:32,000
very well this time.

391
00:22:32,309 --> 00:22:34,910
Looks like you'll need
to win lots more awards.

392
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:37,420
Weren't you just with Bailing?

393
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:38,400
Swimming.

394
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:39,650
Swimming's a popular

395
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:41,190
extra credit item lately.

396
00:22:41,299 --> 00:22:43,299
Isn't that just what you're good at?

397
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:45,339
Since hitting my head,

398
00:22:46,730 --> 00:22:47,660
I can't anymore.

399
00:22:49,289 --> 00:22:50,519
Xia Zefang,

400
00:22:50,690 --> 00:22:52,470
it's like riding a bike.

401
00:22:52,849 --> 00:22:54,779
If you don't ride for a long time,
you'll be scared.

402
00:22:54,779 --> 00:22:56,680
But our bodies have memory.

403
00:23:19,450 --> 00:23:19,789
[Next Episode Preview]

404
00:23:19,789 --> 00:23:20,859
You're still mad?

405
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:22,700
Quit acting pitiful.

406
00:23:23,259 --> 00:23:24,190
If you're a man,

407
00:23:24,220 --> 00:23:25,690
show your true heart.

408
00:23:26,730 --> 00:23:28,400
Just let me hold you, that's all.

409
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,269
So it's true

410
00:23:29,269 --> 00:23:31,039
that love really changes people.

411
00:23:31,039 --> 00:23:32,299
Who said we're in love?

412
00:23:32,569 --> 00:23:33,339
You're not?

413
00:23:33,799 --> 00:23:35,880
You two even sleep hugging each other.

414
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,380
Haiyuan's mine.

415
00:23:37,650 --> 00:23:38,490
Do you dare?

416
00:23:38,579 --> 00:23:39,880
Loser has to do

417
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,210
whatever the winner says.

418
00:23:41,210 --> 00:23:41,849
Bet's on.

419
00:23:41,849 --> 00:23:42,650
Who's afraid?

420
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,319
What do I do?

421
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:46,039
I think…

422
00:23:46,650 --> 00:23:47,690
I like you too much.